Enjoying the clean fruit at Yamanashi in Japan
In countless destinations to discover Japan, it will be missing if you do not visit the "Kingdom of Fruit" named Yamanashi, which is famous for largest production of peaches, pears and grapes in Japan. This summer, visitors will admire the lush orchards freely and pick the ripe fruit by hand enjoy at the garden.
Yamanashi is a central province of Japan, located adjacent to Tokyo to the west. The rich land all year-round is supplied fresh fruit lot within throughout Japan. Besides fruit, it is also known for Koshu wines made from scrumptious Koshu grapes. We can say, Yamanashi is also a birthplace of renowned wine production in Japan.
